metadata.name: Strange Impression #47
metadata.description:
Skewed concrete poetry.
Typography created by laying multiple layers of typewriter effect characters on top of each other
Features one of six possible character types
4 possible text colors for each section
5 possible dark paper colors including rare red (10% chance)
3 styles of paper grain
Differing line gaps and amount of layers
Differing types of skew effect
Differing types of blend effect when characters overlay.

Press S to save in High Resolution

Uses p5.js and scribble.js
@p1x3lboy July 2022

metadata.name: Through the Maze #11
metadata.description:
Constructing the pillars of life
Sculpted with fragments of time
Written on parchments of sky
Revealing the poetry of the gods

Between congruent representations of time
Exists a gap of complex irreverent forms
An anarchy of the body and the senses
Lying between the absurd and the sublime.

Project created using fractal art + code + chaos theory to generate unusual structures and geometries within fractals.

metadata.name: PIPES #128
metadata.description:
PIPES are its own creatures growing out of an Octree, swirling and twirling towards each's individual destination.  

Features:   
  There are four different flow modes, seven different palettes.   
  PIPES can either be hollow or filled, and there is a small chance the PIPES is drawn in gradient.  

Loading time is about 6s and then it will start to animate. Thank you for your patience.  

Press 'S' to save a high resolution 4800x4800px PNG of the artwork.  

This work is made purely with p5js.

metadata.name: Angel's Egg #159
metadata.description:
Perfect life forms descending from the heavens.
Rebirth, a chance to be born again.



Open in live mode for optimal viewing.

Press 's' in live mode to save a 2400 x 4000 resolution image of the piece.

metadata.name: the boxes we live in #253
metadata.description:
Throughout our lives we are placed in boxes that define who we are and limit how we think of ourselves. 

I am a father, husband, son, brother, friend. I am an artist, programmer, photographer, musician, designer, creator. I am a student and I am a teacher. I am a good person. I am a bad person. I am a human.

What boxes do you put yourself in, and do you let others put you in? Is it possible to break out of the boxes that define your life? Do you even want to? What's outside of these boundaries? What is at the center?

metadata.name: 1888 - Spatter #3
metadata.description:
Generative paintings based on the abstract expressionism of Jackson Pollock. 

Various curves and ellipses are used to generate different spatter that are painted using the color of my photographs.

Press "s" to save the image.

metadata.name: Migration #43
metadata.description:
"Migration" is a generative work with which I want to ease my worries about the irresponsibility of people towards the planet they live on.
If we migrate, I hope it will be for the purpose of exploring new areas and not because we have destroyed the planet we live on and are now forced to flee.

Created with 100% p5.js code and math.

Hi-res. options:

- press 'i' to save .png with resolution = 1000px x 1000px
- press 't' to save .png with resolution = 2000px x 2000px
- press 's' to save .png with resolution = 6000px x 6000px


@Mutart, July, 2022.
